      "span_text": "The fatty acid desaturase technically called as oleoyl phosphatidylcholine (oleoyl-PC) desaturase (FAD2) is the enzyme responsible for the conversion of oleic acid to linoleic acid by the insertion of double bond in to the hydrocarbon chain"
